## Known Gotchas (recurring upstream regressions)

These are upstream behaviors that keep silently re-breaking the fork across
nightly syncs. Each one is covered by a patch above — if the patch stops
working, audit this list before writing a new patch.

### `engines.vscode` bump

Upstream tracks VS Code Insiders and regularly bumps `package.json` →
`engines.vscode` (e.g. `^1.118.0`, `^1.119.0`). If this ships to the fork
without being clamped, installing the `.vsix` on VS Code Stable fails with:

> Error: Unable to install extension 'github.copilot-chat' as it is not
> compatible with VS Code '1.116.0'.

**Fix:** Covered by **Patch 3**, which forces `engines.vscode = "^1.116.0"`
on every sync. If you intentionally want to bump the floor (e.g. because you
want to use a new `vscode` API), update Patch 3 — never edit `package.json`
directly, the nightly sync will undo it.

### Gemini SDK error ergonomics

The `@google/genai` SDK throws `ApiError` whose `.message` is the raw HTTP
JSON body. It also has no built-in retries for 429/503. Without Patches 7+8
applied, chat UI shows `Reason: {"error":{"code":503,...}}` and fails
immediately on transient 503s.

**Fix:** Patches 7 and 8 in `geminiNativeProvider.ts`. Patch 8 depends on
Patch 7 — if you rewrite Patch 7, re-check Patch 8's anchors.

### Fake token 401 spam

When running in fully offline BYOK mode the fake Copilot token 401s against
`api.githubcopilot.com`, causing log spam and retry hot-loops in
`modelMetadataFetcher.ts` and friends.

**Fix:** Patches 1 and 5 add short-circuits for `copilotToken === 'fake-token'`.

**Subtle perf trap** (fixed in Patch 5): the short-circuit must NOT fire
`_onDidModelRefresh`. In BYOK-only mode `_familyMap` stays empty, so
`_shouldRefreshModels()` returns `true` on every call. If the bypass fires
the refresh event, `languageModelAccess`'s listener re-queries models →
re-enters `_fetchModels` → fires the event again. Cheap per-iteration but
cumulatively slows VS Code. Patch 5 also sets a `_fakeTokenShortCircuited`
flag so subsequent calls return immediately without even awaiting
`getCopilotToken()`.

### Cross-provider tool-call ID incompatibility

Anthropic validates `tool_use.id` and `tool_result.tool_use_id` against
`^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. Gemini emits ids containing `.`, `/`, etc. When a user
switches mid-conversation from Gemini to Claude (or Vertex-Claude), the
historical tool-call ids flow through unchanged and Anthropic 400s with:

> messages.N.content.M.tool_use.id: String should match pattern
> '^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$'

**Fix:** Patch 17 exports a deterministic `sanitizeAnthropicToolId` helper
used at both the `tool_use` and `tool_result` emission sites in
`anthropicMessageConverter.ts`. Valid ids pass through unchanged; invalid
ones get `_`-replaced plus an FNV-1a hash suffix so distinct original ids
don't collapse to the same sanitized string.

### Cross-provider tool-name resolution (Anthropic → Gemini)

The mirror image of the above. Anthropic's `tool_use.id` (`toolu_01ABC…`)
and OpenAI's (`call_XYZ`) carry no tool name. When the user switches
mid-conversation from Sonnet to a Gemini BYOK model, every
`LanguageModelToolResultPart` in history has only a callId, not a name.
The Gemini converter's legacy `callId.split('_')[0]` heuristic was
designed for Gemini-native `functionName_timestamp` ids and collapses
every Anthropic tool response to `name: 'toolu'`. Gemini rejects with:

> Please ensure that the number of function response parts is equal to
> the number of function call parts of the function call turn.

(Deceptive — it's really about names not matching, not counts.)

**Fix:** Patch 43 pre-walks the transcript, builds a `callId → name` map
from every `LanguageModelToolCallPart`, and exposes `resolveToolName()`
which looks up the map first and falls back to the legacy split only
when the map has no entry.

### Internal model family lookups throwing in BYOK-only mode

Several code paths hard-code an internal Copilot model family and call
`getChatEndpoint('copilot-base')` / `getChatEndpoint('copilot-fast')` (the
latter aliases to `gpt-4o-mini`). Under the fake-token bypass these lookups
throw because `modelMetadataFetcher._familyMap` / `_copilotBaseModel` are
never populated. Symptoms users see:

> Error: Unable to resolve chat model with family selection: copilot-base  
> Error: Unable to resolve chat model with family selection: gpt-4o-mini

The second one is particularly sneaky because it only surfaces when the
workspace registers ≳128 tools (e.g. Pylance + Looker MCP + Tableau MCP all
loaded), tipping `VirtualToolGrouper` into its LLM-summarization path.

**Fix:** Patch 15 reorders `switchToBaseModel` to short-circuit BYOK / free
/ non-copilot requests before the `copilot-base` lookup. Patch 16 wraps the
`copilot-fast` lookup in `_generateBulkGroupDescriptions` in try/catch and
falls back to deterministic group descriptions so chat turns still complete.
Patch 18 covers the third (and most impactful) site: `renderPromptElementJSON`
in `promptRenderer.ts`, which every built-in file tool routes through. Without
it the chat looks superficially healthy (turns complete, model answers) but
`read_file` / `list_dir` / `file_search` / `grep_search` / `get_errors` /
edits via `codeMapper` all fail with "Unable to resolve chat model with family
selection: copilot-base", typically manifesting as the assistant blaming MCP,
workspace indexing, or your Copilot subscription for a problem that is
entirely in the BYOK fake-token path.
